docs/Malaria_Project_Report.md# Malaria Detection using Deep Learning - Project Report

## Project Overview
Automated malaria detection system using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) to classify microscopic blood smear images as infected or uninfected.

## Team
- Team Lead: Soumya Ray
- Members: Vansh Kumar Singh, Aarzoo Yadav, Aditya Raj

## Results
- Test Accuracy: 93.8%
- Precision: 93.2%
- Recall: 94.0%
- F1 Score: 93.6%
- Prediction Latency: <2 seconds per image

## Technologies Used
- Deep Learning: TensorFlow/Keras, CNN
- Image Processing: OpenCV, NumPy
- Web Framework: Flask, Python
- Data Visualization: Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Version Control: GitHub

## Key Features
- Automated detection of malaria parasites from cell images
- High-accuracy binary classification (Parasitized vs. Uninfected)
- Interactive web interface for image upload and result display
- Data visualization dashboards for model performance metrics
- Lightweight and scalable model suitable for low-resource environments
